examples.en: This vaccine is already routinely used.
A brisk walk is part of her morning routine.
The job will be easier once you settle into a routine.
Students at the private school were once routinely birched for violating the rules.
He criticized her routine absence from important meetings.
Data entry becomes routine very quickly.
Grandma gets upset if we change her routine.
The city's firefighters routinely put their lives in jeopardy by executing daring rescues.
That tabloid routinely publishes the most moronically mendacious stories about celebrities.
The surgery has become a very routine operation and poses little danger.
The sediment at the bottom of the river needs to be routinely dredged so that it doesn't interfere with barge traffic.
They hire high-school students for routine work such as filing.
The more you do it, the more routine it becomes.
